text: Mirachelus clinocnemus is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chilodontidae. ==Description== The size of the shell varies between 2 mm and 4.5 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean from Florida to Eastern Brasil. ==References== * Rosenberg, G., F. Moretzsohn, and E. F. García. 2009. Gastropoda (Mollusca) of the Gulf of Mexico, Pp. 579–699 in Felder, D.L. and D.K. Camp (eds.), Gulf of Mexico–Origins, Waters, and Biota. Biodiversity. Texas A&M; Press, College Station, Texas ==External links== * clinocnemus Category:Gastropods described in 1979
title: Mirachelus clinocnemus
